ORIGINALITY STATEMENT:

CRYS-L is an entirely original language created by Percy Rojas Masgo.

1. LANGUAGE DESIGN — Original:
   The CRYS-L grammar, syntax, and keyword set were designed from scratch
   by Percy Rojas Masgo in 2025-2026. Key syntactic constructs that are
   unique to CRYS-L and do not exist in any other language:
     - plan_name(...) { } — plan declaration block
     - formula "name": "expression" ; — named formula declaration
     - assert expr msg "..." ; — assertion with inline message
     - output id label "..." unit "..." ; — annotated output declaration
     - meta { standard: "...", source: "...", domain: "..." } — metadata block
   No part of the grammar or syntax was copied or derived from any
   other language, DSL, or software project.

2. NAME — Original:
   "CRYS-L" (with hyphen) does not exist as a name for any other language,
   DSL, library, or software project. Note: "CrySL" (no hyphen, different
   capitalization) is an unrelated academic DSL for cryptographic API
   specification (ECOOP 2018, Fraunhofer/TU Darmstadt) — different domain,
   different syntax, different purpose. CRYS-L has no relationship to it.

3. STANDARD LIBRARY CODE — Original:
   All .crysl files in stdlib/ are original implementations by Percy Rojas Masgo.
   Engineering formulas are mathematical laws in the public domain.
   No code was copied from any existing language, framework, or library.
   Standard references (NFPA, IEC, ACI, IS.010) appear by name and section
   number only — no verbatim text copied from copyrighted standard documents.

4. COMPILER AND RUNTIME — Original:
   The CRYS-L compiler and WASM runtime are original implementations.
   They were built specifically for this language and do not derive from
   any existing compiler framework, LLVM IR, or third-party toolchain.

5. CONTRIBUTIONS:
   Pull Request contributors agree their work is original and submitted
   under this same MIT License.

